m_\";a:6:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:167:\"Roles and responsibilities are clearly defined for the following ITSM processes: Change Management, Incident/Problem Management, Asset Management, Knowledge Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:91:\"ITSM processes have clearly defined Inputs, Outputs, Controls, Measurements, and Activities\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:40:\"Tools are used to support ITSM processes\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:85:\"ITSM processes interface with each other from a both a process and people perspective\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:53:\"ITSM effectiveness is measured using reports and SLAs\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:58:\"ITSM service delivery meets or exceeds defined objectives \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}s:76:\"sections_operations_tables_data_classification_questions_data_classification\";a:5:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:113:\"Data Classification regulations, compliance requirements, and standards have been identified for the organization\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:113:\"A Data Classification process has been enabled using an industry excepted protection model (e.g. high/medium/low)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:79:\"Data asset owners have been identified including data custodians for each asset\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:121:\"Data retention, recovery, and disposal policies have been defined as part of the overarching data classification strategy\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:61:\"Data protection standards have been developed and implemented\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}s:96:\"sections_operations_tables_disaster_recovery__dr__backup_questions_disaster_recovery__dr__backup\";a:9:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:101:\"A complete list of systems has been documented including signed-off business impact analysis’ (BIA)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:86:\