s:4:\"desc\";s:158:\"Do you have an overarching IT governance framework that assigns appropriate decision making rights to the right groups, are the right people making decisions?\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:37:\"Executive Level IT Steering Committee\";s:4:\"desc\";s:100:\"Do you have a functional IT Steering Committee that engages the Executive level of the organization?\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Corporate IT Working Committees\";s:4:\"desc\";s:105:\"Do you have a range of cross functional coordinating groups that help guide decision making and strategy?\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"IT Strategic Plan\";s:4:\"desc\";s:80:\"Do you have a history of developing strategic plans, do you have a current plan?\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"IT Tactical Plans\";s:4:\"desc\";s:101:\"Are you satisfied that you have a current / required range of tactical IT plans, what gaps are there?\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"IT Policies\";s:4:\"desc\";s:192:\"Do you have an appropriate policy framework and policies; should at minimum include Acceptable use, IT Security, Asset lifecycle, Data management, IT procurement processes, Backup and Restore?\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"IT Standards\";s:4:\"desc\";s:42:\"Have you defined appropriate IT standards?\";}i:8;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:37:\"IT Performance Measures and Reporting\";s:4:\"desc\";s:86:\"Have you developed corporate and IT management level performance measures and reports?\";}i:9;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"IT Risk Management Framework\";s:4:\"desc\";s:98:\"Do you have an IT risk management framework, and do you regularly assess and report upon IT risks?\";}}s:83:\"sections_it_management_tables_it_service_management_questions_it_service_management\";a:17:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Service Desk\";s:4:\"desc\";s:150:\"You have established a central point of contact that operates as a full service desk to the organization for IT support, requests and new requirements\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Registration of Customer Queries\";s:4:\"desc\";s:289:\"You have defined a standardized process for logging requests (email, online), you have a standard method of classification of requests and associated service levels that define response and resolution expectations, customers can track and monitor allocation and progress with their request\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:27:\"Incident Escalation Process\";s:4:\"desc\";s:225:\"You have defined internal escalation processes that allow requests to be escalated to other groups within IT, and for supervisors to identify and follow up on incidents that may be approaching parameters that you have defined\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"Incident Closure\";s:4:\"desc\";s:182:\"You have a standardized process for incident closure that allows the customer to confirm that the issue has been resolved, and that allows the customer to rate the service experience\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"Reporting and Trend Analysis\";s:4:\"desc\";s:168:\"You have defined management metrics for IT management use, and review them regularly within the IT management team, you also share high level metrics with IT governance\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"IT Asset Management (ITAM)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:221:\"You have developed processes that provide an accurate account of technology asset lifecycle costs and risks to maximize the business value of technology strategy, architecture, funding, contractual and sourcing decisions.\";}i:17;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:40:\"Configuration Management Database (CMDB)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:67:\"You have a centralized configuration system to manage all IT assets\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Knowledge Base\";s:4:\"desc\";s:70:\"You maintain a knowledge base of resolutions to incidents and problems\";}i:8;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Problem Tracking and Resolution\";s:4:\"desc\";s:116:\"You have defined and operate a problem management process and track problems and resolutions within your ITSM system\";}i:9;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:63:\"IT Support Services are Available Outside of ‘office hours’\";s:4:\"desc\";s:210:\"You have defined a business model that allows the IT department to provide effective support outside of standard 8:30 – 5:00 hours, this may include extended hours, shifts, call out schedule and payment terms\";}i:10;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"Service Catalog\";s:4:\"desc\";s:188:\"You have defined the services that are provided by the IT department, you have published a document or intranet site that details how to access the services, what to expect, what costs are\";}i:11;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"SLA’s or OLA’s\";s:4:\"desc\";s:132:\"You have defined and actively use SLA’s or OLA’s to define, agree and communicate service levels provided by the IT organization\";}i:12;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:48:\"Monitoring and Reporting Against SLA and OLA’s\";s:4:\"desc\";s:81:\"You monitor and report against SLA performance to IT management and IT governance\";}i:13;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Change Standards and Procedures\";s:4:\"desc\";s:164:\"You have a standardized process for identifying, planning, reviewing, approving changes made to the technology environment, this may include a Change Advisory Board\";}i:14;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:36:\"Change Status Tracking and Reporting\";s:4:\"desc\";s:132:\"You track, analyse and regularly report (to management and governance) on change management compliance / performance / effectiveness\";}i:15;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Known Maintenance Window\";s:4:\"desc\";s:88:\"You have defined a standard window(s) for applying changes to the technology environment\";}i:16;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Change Communication\";s:4:\"desc\";s:109:\"You have a standardized corporate communications method for communicating about planned and emergency changes\";}}s:101:\"sections_it_management_tables_project_and_program_management_questions_project_and_program_management\";a:5:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"Standardized Opportunity Intake Process\";s:4:\"desc\";s:188:\"Do you have an agreed upon method for the intake of technology opportunities that applies appropriate due diligence based on the size of the opportunity -  includes cost-benefit evaluation\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:41:\"Prioritization / Ranking of Opportunities\";s:4:\"desc\";s:101:\"Do you have an agreed upon corporate method for rating, ranking and selecting technology investments?\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"Project Management Framework\";s:4:\"desc\";s:99:\"Do you have a standardized project methodology that is consistently applied to technology projects?\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:54:\"Project Portfolio Performance Reporting and Monitoring\";s:4:\"desc\";s:157:\"Do you have a standardized, corporately recognized way of reporting on the complete project portfolio to the IT team, steering committee and the corporation?\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Resource Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:144:\"Do you have resource management capabilities that allow you to track and manage resource capacity, resource allocation and resource utilization?\";}}s:91:\"sections_it_management_tables_architecture_and_roadmaps_questions_architecture_and_roadmaps\";a:10:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Information and Data Architecture\";s:4:\"desc\";s:84:\"Do you have an agreed corporate information and data architecture, or parts thereof?\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"Technology Architecture\";s:4:\"desc\";s:74:\"Do you have an agreed corporate technology architecture, or parts thereof?\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Application Architecture\";s:4:\"desc\";s:65:\"Do you have an agreed application architecture, or parts thereof?\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"IT Architecture Board\";s:4:\"desc\";s:91:\"Do you have a team that is responsible for maintaining and reviewing architectural changes?\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Data Classification Scheme\";s:4:\"desc\";s:51:\"Do you have a corporate data classification scheme?\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Key IT Infrastructure Roadmaps\";s:4:\"desc\";s:155:\"Have you identified your key IT infrastructure platforms and do you maintain multi-year roadmaps, and forward looking plans for your key IT infrastructure?\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Key Business Application Roadmaps\";s:4:\"desc\";s:165:\"Have you identified your key IT business application platforms and do you maintain multi-year roadmaps, and forward looking plans for your key business applications?\";}i:8;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Technology Standards\";s:4:\"desc\";s:248:\"Do have a method of establishing, and have you established documented technology guidelines and standards, advice on infrastructure products and guidance on the selection of technology, do you measure compliance with these standards and guidelines?\";}i:10;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Web and Digital Strategy\";s:4:\"desc\";s:37:\"Do you have a Web / Digital strategy?\";}i:11;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:35:\"Monitoring Future Technology Trends\";s:4:\"desc\";s:119:\"Do you have a suitable program for R&D that allows you to monitor, evaluate and on-board new and emerging technologies?\";}}s:73:\"sections_it_management_tables_business_systems_questions_business_systems\";a:7:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"New System Requirements Gathering\";s:4:\"desc\";s:117:\"Do you follow standard, repeatable and corporately understood business processes for developing systems requirements?\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Feasibility Studies\";s:4:\"desc\";s:90:\"Do you have a standard practice and associated process for conducting feasibility studies?\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:44:\"Requirements Decision and Approval Processes\";s:4:\"desc\";s:92:\"Do you follow standard process for reviewing, finalizing and approving systems requirements?\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"Acquisition Processes\";s:4:\"desc\";s:71:\"Do you follow standard process for selecting and acquiring new systems?\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:54:\"Configuration and Implementation of Business Solutions\";s:4:\