tion that contains at a minimum backup and recovery, incident and problem management, security management, configuration management of critical systems, change control process management?\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:40:\"Project to Operations Knowledge Transfer\";s:4:\"desc\";s:117:\"Do you have standardized processes that ensure that project knowledge is effectively transferred to operations staff?\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Performance and Capacity Planning\";s:4:\"desc\";s:205:\"Do you regularly and proactively review performance and conduct short, medium and long term capacity planning for the technology infrastructure, are capacity plans shared with IT management and governance?\";}}s:71:\"sections_it_management_tables_data_management_questions_data_management\";a:6:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Data and Systems Ownership\";s:4:\"desc\";s:120:\"Is there clear corporate understanding (supported by policy) upon systems and data ownership roles and responsibilities?\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:49:\"Data Storage, Retention and Archival Requirements\";s:4:\"desc\";s:147:\"Linked to the data classification, do you have clearly documented (possibly in policy) definition of storage, retention and retirement time frames?\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:63:\"Technology Solutions to Support Storage, Retention and Archival\";s:4:\"desc\";s:110:\"Do you have technology solutions to implement data storage, retention and archival needs of the organization??\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Data Disposal Arrangements\";s:4:\"desc\";s:116:\"Do you have processes in place to ensure that sensitive data is protected when software and hardware is disposed of?\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Backup and Restore Arrangements\";s:4:\"desc\";s:212:\"Do you have a corporate policy related to backup and restore (and clear corporate understanding) of backup provisions, do you have appropriate solutions ensuring that all business data is appropriately backed up?\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Offsite backup / storage\";s:4:\"desc\";s:50:\"Do you have appropriate offsite backup provisions?\";}}s:99:\"sections_it_management_tables_data_and_services_portability_questions_data_and_services_portability\";a:6:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"Application Portability\";s:4:\"desc\";s:218:\"A plan has been developed to ensure the current cloud provider format will be accepted for all application artifacts and support all application dependencies - e.g. new vendor will accept the same format of VM image \r\n\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Data Export Formats\";s:4:\"desc\";s:99:\"Does the current vendor provide interoperable  export formats for all data stored within the cloud?\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"Data Portability and Interoperability Strategy \";s:4:\"desc\";s:126:\"An Enterprise strategy is in place for data portability and interoperability that encompasses both current and future states .\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:37:\"Portability: Technology and Standards\";s:4:\"desc\";s:155:\"Your current provider uses virtualization or container technology to package up applications and data - providing flexibility to move within hybrid clouds.\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"Testing Procedures\";s:4:\"desc\";s:120:\"Are there processes for testing that data can be exported to another cloud provider - should OPB wish to change vendors?\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Security: Data and Applications\";s:4:\"desc\";s:158:\"Cloud interoperable security policies are formally documented (e.g. authentication controls, encryption, data classification, data integrity measures, etc.)\r\n\";}}s:101:\"sections_it_management_tables_business_continuity_management_questions_business_continuity_management\";a:5:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:41:\"Corporate DR and Business Continuity Plan\";s:4:\"desc\";s:146:\"Do you have a Senior Management agreed DR and BC plan, that has effectively prioritized corporate needs, key systems, RTO and RPO for key systems?\";}i:2;a:2:{s