Risk Management Framework\";s:4:\"desc\";s:97:\"do you have an IT risk management framework, and do you regularly assess and report upon IT risks\";}}s:81:\"sections_it_management_tables_financial_management_questions_financial_management\";a:3:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"IT Budget Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:179:\"do you effectively monitor budget vs. actuals at a project and portfolio level, do you actively monitor at the IT Management level, do you provide reporting at the Executive level\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:29:\"Cost Management / Re-charging\";s:4:\"desc\";s:105:\"do you have a clear, transparent widely understood and consistent cost recovery / cost allocation process\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:34:\"Benefit Management and Realization\";s:4:\"desc\";s:166:\"do you have a benefits management tracking program that allows you to track, monitor and report on the realization of benefits declared in investment / business cases\";}}s:101:\"sections_it_management_tables_project_and_program_management_questions_project_and_program_management\";a:5:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"Standardized Opportunity Intake Process\";s:4:\"desc\";s:219:\"do you have an agreed upon method for the intake of technology opportunities that applies appropriate due diligence based on the size of the opportunity, do you evaluate the cost-benefit associated with each opportunity\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:41:\"Prioritization / Ranking of Opportunities\";s:4:\"desc\";s:100:\"do you have an agreed upon corporate method for rating, ranking and selecting technology investments\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"Project Management Framework\";s:4:\"desc\";s:98:\"do you have a standardized project methodology that is consistently applied to technology projects\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:54:\"Project Portfolio Performance Reporting and Monitoring\";s:4:\"desc\";s:156:\"do you have a standardized, corporately recognized way of reporting on the complete project portfolio to the IT team, steering committee and the corporation\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Resource Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:143:\"do you have resource management capabilities that allow you to track and manage resource capacity, resource allocation and resource utilization\";}}s:91:\"sections_it_management_tables_architecture_and_roadmaps_questions_architecture_and_roadmaps\";a:11:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Information and Data Architecture\";s:4:\"desc\";s:83:\"do you have an agreed corporate information and data architecture, or parts thereof\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"Technology Architecture\";s:4:\"desc\";s:73:\"do you have an agreed corporate technology architecture, or parts thereof\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Application Architecture\";s:4:\"desc\";s:64:\"do you have an agreed application architecture, or parts thereof\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"IT Architecture Board\";s:4:\"desc\";s:90:\"do you have a team that is responsible for maintaining and reviewing architectural changes\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Data Classification Scheme\";s:4:\"desc\";s:50:\"do you have a corporate data classification scheme\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Key IT Infrastructure Roadmaps\";s:4:\"desc\";s:154:\"have you identified your key IT infrastructure platforms and do you maintain multi-year roadmaps, and forward looking plans for your key IT infrastructure\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Key Business Application Roadmaps\";s:4:\"desc\";s:164:\"have you identified your key IT business application platforms and do you maintain multi-year roadmaps, and forward looking plans for your key business applications\";}i:8;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Technology Standards\";s:4:\"desc\";s:247:\"do have a method of establishing, and have you established documented technology guidelines and standards, advice on infrastructure products and guidance on the selection of technology, do you measure compliance with these standards and guidelines\";}i:9;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"GIS Strategy\";s:4:\"desc\";s:26:\"do you have a GIS strategy\";}i:10;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Web and Digital Strategy\";s:4:\"desc\";s:36:\"do you have a Web / Digital strategy\";}i:11;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:35:\"Monitoring Future Technology Trends\";s:4:\"desc\";s:117:\"do you have a suitable program for R&D that allows you to monitor, evaluate and onboard new and emerging technologies\";}}s:71:\"sections_it_management_tables_it_organization_questions_it_organization\";a:10:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"IT Organization Placement\";s:4:\"desc\";s:64:\"is the IT leader reporting relationship at the appropriate level\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"IT Leadership\";s:4:\"desc\";s:82:\"is the IT leader a member of the corporation’s senior leadership/management team\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"IT Organization Structure\";s:4:\"desc\";s:44:\"is the IT organization structure appropriate\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:11:\"IT Staffing\";s:4:\"desc\";s:71:\"does the IT team have the required staffing, are there particular gaps?\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:61:\"Appropriate Organizational Alignment Between IT and GIS staff\";s:4:\"desc\";s:104:\"is there appropriate alignment between GIS and IT resources and clear roles and responsibilities defined\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:61:\"Appropriate Organizational Alignment Between IT and Web Staff\";s:4:\"desc\";s:104:\"is there appropriate alignment between Web and IT resources and clear roles and responsibilities defined\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:73:\"Appropriate Organizational Alignment Between IT and Departmental IT Staff\";s:4:\"desc\";s:116:\"is there appropriate alignment between departmental IT and IT resources and clear roles and responsibilities defined\";}i:8;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"IT Personnel Competencies\";s:4:\"desc\";s:69:\"does the IT team have the required skills, are there particular gaps?\";}i:9;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"IT Personnel Training\";s:4:\"desc\";s:192:\"does the corporation allocate appropriate / adequate funding for technology staff training, do you have individualized training plans, do you get to the training that you plan to do each year?\";}i:10;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Business Relationship Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:242:\"do you proactively manage relationships with departmental stakeholders – e.g. hold regularly scheduled leadership meetings with director’s of business units, service management reviews (i.e. review incidents, projects (planned and future)\";}}s:73:\"sections_it_management_tables_business_systems_questions_business_systems\";a:7:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"New System Requirements Gathering\";s:4:\"desc\";s:116:\"do you follow standard, repeatable and corporately understood business processes for developing systems requirements\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Feasibility Studies\";s:4:\"desc\";s:89:\"do you have a standard practice and associated process for conducting feasibility studies\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:44:\"Requirements Decision and Approval Processes\";s:4:\"desc\";s:91:\"do you follow standard process for reviewing, finalizing and approving systems requirements\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"Acquisition Processes\";s:4:\"desc\";s:70:\"do you follow standard process for selecting and acquiring new systems\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:54:\"Configuration and Implementation of Business Solutions\";s:4:\"desc\";s:92:\"do you follow standard practices and processes configuring and implementing business systems\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:36:\"Business Solutions Test Environments\";s:4:\"desc\";s:68:\"do you have suitable test environments for your key business systems\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"Upgrades to Existing Systems\";s:4:\"desc\";s:182:\"do you have a roadmap and planned timelines for systems upgrades, do you have a policy that determines the frequency and timelines within which upgrades to systems will be conducted?\";}}s:91:\"sections_it_management_tables_technology_infrastructure_questions_technology_infrastructure\";a:7:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Technology Infrastructure Roadmap\";s:4:\"desc\";s:216:\"do you have a multi-year plan for the acquisition, implementation, maintenance, upgrade, and decommissioning of technology infrastructure to meet the business functional and technical requirements of the organization\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Infrastructure Maintenance Plans\";s:4:\"desc\";s:202:\"do you have a plan for infrastructure maintenance that includes periodic reviews against business needs, patch management, upgrade strategies, risks, vulnerabilities assessment and security requirements\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"Infrastructure Monitoring\";s:4:\"desc\";s:238:\"do you proactively monitor key infrastructure platforms, have you identified alerts and messaging to provide sufficient insight into performance of infrastructure to allow you to proactively identify and troubleshoot infrastructure issues\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Infrastructure Test Environments\";s:4:\"desc\";s:78:\"do you have and actively maintain appropriate infrastructure test environments\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:38:\"Operations Procedures and Instructions\";s:4:\"desc\";s:356:\"do you maintain appropriate SOP’s and documentation for your infrastructure, do you maintain a wiki based (easy to edit and maintain) centralized source of IT documentation that contains at a minimum backup and recovery, incident and problem management, security management, configuration management of critical systems, change control process management\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:40:\"Project to Operations Knowledge Transfer\";s:4:\"desc\";s:116:\"do you have standardized processes that ensure that project knowledge is effectively transferred to operations staff\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"Performance and Capacity Planning\";s:4:\"desc\";s:204:\"do you regularly and proactively review performance and conduct short, medium and long term capacity planning for the technology infrastructure, are capacity plans shared with IT management and governance\";}}s:71:\"sections_it_management_tables_data_management_questions_data_management\";a:6:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Data and Systems Ownership\";s:4:\"desc\";s:119:\"is there clear corporate understanding (supported by policy) upon systems and data ownership roles and responsibilities\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:49:\"Data Storage, Retention and Archival Requirements\";s:4:\"desc\";s:146:\"linked to the data classification, do you have clearly documented (possibly in policy) definition of storage, retention and retirement time frames\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:63:\"Technology Solutions to Support Storage, Retention and Archival\";s:4:\"desc\";s:109:\"do you have technology solutions to implement data storage, retention and archival needs of the organization?\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Data Disposal Arrangements\";s:4:\"desc\";s:115:\"do you have processes in place to ensure that sensitive data is protected when software and hardware is disposed of\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Backup and Restore Arrangements\";s:4:\"desc\";s:211:\"do you have a corporate policy related to backup and restore (and clear corporate understanding) of backup provisions, do you have appropriate solutions ensuring that all business data is appropriately backed up\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Offsite backup / storage\";s:4:\"desc\";s:49:\"do you have appropriate offsite backup provisions\";}}s:101:\"sections_it_management_tables_business_continuity_management_questions_business_continuity_management\";a:5:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:41:\"Corporate DR and Business Continuity Plan\";s:4:\"desc\";s:145:\"do you have a Senior Management agreed DR and BC plan, that has effectively prioritized corporate needs, key systems, RTO and RPO for key systems\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:29:\"Business Impact Questionnaire\";s:4:\"desc\";s:52:\"do you have a Business Impact Analysis Questionnaire\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"DR Checklist\";s:4:\"desc\";s:26:\"do you have a DR checklist\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"IT Continuity Plans\";s:4:\"desc\";s:64:\"have you implemented technology solutions to meet the DR/BC plan\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Testing of IT Continuity Plans\";s:4:\"desc\";s:96:\"do you regularly and completely test your IT continuity plans in a complete and effective manner\";}}s:63:\"sections_it_management_tables_procurement_questions_procurement\";a:4:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"Procurement Processes\";s:4:\"desc\";s:160:\"you use known and standardized procurement processes for IT procurement, the procurement team understands technology procurement requirements and supports needs\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Supplier and Contract Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:111:\"you maintain lists of suppliers and contracts, and are able to monitor and manage contract renewals effectively\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"Contract Review\";s:4:\"desc\";s:52:\"do you regularly review annual maintenance contracts\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Supplier Relationship Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:61:\"you actively manage relationships with suppliers and partners\";}}s:57:\"sections_it_management_tables_training_questions_training\";a:2:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:42:\"Identification of Corporate Training Needs\";s:4:\"desc\";s:89:\"you have a process for identifying and developing a corporate technology training program\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:29:\"Delivery of End-user Training\";s:4:\"desc\";s:183:\"you have clearly identified roles and responsibilities for the delivery of end-user training related to technology, productivity, business systems and an effective program of delivery\";}}s:83:\"sections_it_management_tables_it_service_management_questions_it_service_management\";a:16:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Service Desk\";s:4:\"desc\";s:150:\"you have established a central point of contact that operates as a full service desk to the organization for IT support, requests and new requirements\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"Registration of Customer Queries\";s:4:\"desc\";s:289:\"you have defined a standardized process for logging requests (email, online), you have a standard method of classification of requests and associated service levels that define response and resolution expectations, customers can track and monitor allocation and progress with their request\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:27:\"Incident Escalation Process\";s:4:\"desc\";s:225:\"you have defined internal escalation processes that allow requests to be escalated to other groups within IT, and for supervisors to identify and follow up on incidents that may be approaching parameters that you have defined\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"Incident Closure\";s:4:\"desc\";s:182:\"you have a standardized process for incident closure that allows the customer to confirm that the issue has been resolved, and that allows the customer to rate the service experience\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"Reporting and Trend Analysis\";s:4:\"desc\";s:168:\"you have defined management metrics for IT management use, and review them regularly within the IT management team, you also share high level metrics with IT governance\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"Inventory\";s:4:\"desc\";s:153:\"you have a complete and well maintained inventory of all hardware and software licenses, and processes to ensure the ongoing maintenance of the inventory\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Knowledge Base\";s:4:\"desc\";s:70:\"you maintain a knowledge base of resolutions to incidents and problems\";}i:8;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Problem Tracking and Resolution\";s:4:\"desc\";s:116:\"you have defined and operate a problem management process and track problems and resolutions within your ITSM system\";}i:9;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:63:\"IT Support Services are Available Outside of ‘office hours’\";s:4:\"desc\";s:210:\"you have defined a business model that allows the IT department to provide effective support outside of standard 8.30 – 4.30 hours, this may include extended hours, shifts, call out schedule and payment terms\";}i:10;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"Service Catalog\";s:4:\"desc\";s:188:\"you have defined the services that are provided by the IT department, you have published a document or intranet site that details how to access the services, what to expect, what costs are\";}i:11;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:18:\"SLA’s or OLA’s\";s:4:\"desc\";s:132:\"you have defined and actively use SLA’s or OLA’s to define, agree and communicate service levels provided by the IT organization\";}i:12;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:48:\"Monitoring and Reporting Against SLA and OLA’s\";s:4:\"desc\";s:81:\"you monitor and report against SLA performance to IT management and IT governance\";}i:13;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"Change Standards and Procedures\";s:4:\"desc\";s:164:\"you have a standardized process for identifying, planning, reviewing, approving changes made to the technology environment, this may include a Change Advisory Board\";}i:14;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:36:\"Change Status Tracking and Reporting\";s:4:\"desc\";s:132:\"you track, analyse and regularly report (to management and governance) on change management compliance / performance / effectiveness\";}i:15;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Known Maintenance Window\";s:4:\"desc\";s:88:\"you have defined a standard window(s) for applying changes to the technology environment\";}i:16;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Change Communication\";s:4:\"desc\";s:109:\"you have a standardized corporate communications method for communicating about planned and emergency changes\";}}s:63:\"sections_it_management_tables_it_security_questions_it_security\";a:7:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"IT Security Plan\";s:4:\"desc\";s:195:\"you have a corporately agreed IT security plan, with associated policies that defines roles and responsibilities, and a roadmap for implementation and operation of a corporate IT security program\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"Identify Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:93:\"all users and their activity on IT systems are uniquely identifiable, trackable and auditable\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"User Account Management\";s:4:\"desc\";s:273:\"you have standardized and efficient procedures for request, creating, modifying, suspending and closing user accounts and assigning privileges. You have a process that provides an appropriate approval procedure to ensure systems owners provide the appropriate authorization\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:14:\"Access Control\";s:4:\"desc\";s:57:\"do you have access control policies for software and data\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"Network Security\";s:4:\"desc\";s:229:\"do you use appropriate security techniques and related management procedures (e.g., firewalls, security appliances, network segmentation, intrusion detection) to authorise access and control information flows from and to networks\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:17:\"Physical Security\";s:4:\"desc\";s:364:\"have you implemented appropriate physical security measures in line with business requirements to secure the location and the physical assets. Physical security measures must be capable of effectively preventing, detecting and mitigating risks relating to theft, temperature, fire, smoke, water, vibration, terror, vandalism, power outages, chemicals or explosives\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Security Assessments\";s:4:\"desc\";s:119:\"do you conduct regular external security assessments and audits to ensure that your security provisions are appropriate\";}}}'),
