s:67:\" Change Management Policies & Processes Incorporate DR Requirements\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:11;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:85:\"Internal & External Process Dependencies Identified, Documented & Integrated With DR \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:12;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:115:\"Related to working 3rd party providers like MSPs, ensure documentation defines who is responsible for which steps. \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}s:93:\"sections_recovery_planning_tables_recovery_site_assessment_questions_recovery_site_assessment\";a:9:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:67:\"Recovery Site Details - DR Site Environmental & Equipment Specifics\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:70:\" Alternate Site Environment Identified, Equipped & Operationally Ready\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:65:\"Operating Systems Software Environment (Versions, Releases, Etc.)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:122:\"There is sufficient geographic separation between the DR environment and primary data center to meet business requirements\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:77:\" Alternate Site Infrastructure Satisfies Service Levels & Recovery Objectives\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:38:\" Application Flows & Interdependencies\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:7;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:83:\"  External Service Provider (Supplier/Receiver) Connectivity In Place & Operational\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:8;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:75:\"Incident Command Center(s) Identified & Operational – Ready For Occupancy\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:9;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:53:\"Availability Of Alternate Recovery Space(s) For Staff\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}s:96:\"sections_maintenance_sand_improvement_tables_audit_and_compliance_questions_audit_and_compliance\";a:2:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:75:\"Crisis Management (Command & Control Structure) Organization & Plans Exist \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:35:\"Documented Emergency Response Plans\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}s:100:\"sections_maintenance_sand_improvement_tables_testing_and_validation_questions_testing_and_validation\";a:5:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:113:\"Tabletop exercises are conducted (and documented) at least annually and include a variety of potential scenarios \";s:4:\"desc\";s:1:\" \";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:139:\" An immediate debrief as well as a full test review with identified action items is conducted and documented after each DR testing exercise\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:91:\"Confirm what the DRP production capacity is estimated to cover to ensure adequate capacity.\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:240:\" Test and document your failover strategy to see whether your business will be able to recover in your standby DR site and will run applications successfully when your primary site is disengaged (testing must be performed at least annually)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:182:\" Test and document your failback plan to determine that your company will be able to return from the recovery site to the original site. (testing must be performed at least annually)\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}s:114:\"sections_maintenance_sand_improvement_tables_licensing_and_ancillary_costs_questions_licensing_and_ancillary_costs\";a:4:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:162:\" Licensing limits in your application stack has been validated to make sure you have addressed all requirements before putting them in use for any length of time.\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:253:\"If you are working with a managed service provider (MSP) or another third-party vendor to manage data backup and disaster recovery function, review any documentation addressing time restraints on transitioning your environment back to the original site.\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:135:\" Review your operational service level agreements (SLAs) to ensure they will carry over to the DR environment should that be necessary.\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:184:\" Review the potential costs for turning your DR site into a permanent site, which can include failover declaration fees, software, equipment, and facility costs.                       \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}s:100:\"sections_maintenance_sand_improvement_tables_awareness_and_training_questions_awareness_and_training\";a:4:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:65:\"Formalized, Mandatory Corporate DR Program Awareness & Training  \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"The DR team is fully aware of its responsibilities  \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:79:\"The roles and responsibilities of the DR team have been assigned and documented\";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:94:\"Contact information for your DR team is up to date and can be accessed by appropriate parties \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}s:90:\"sections_maintenance_sand_improvement_tables_exercise_programs_questions_exercise_programs\";a:2:{i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:59:\"Business Unit Involvement In Exercise & Validation Program \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:69:\"DR testing exercises are verified by management review and sign-off  \";s:4:\"desc\";s:0:\"\";}}}'),
